name: prolyl oligopeptidase
reaction: Hydrolysis of ---Pro! and to a lesser extent ---Ala! in oligopeptides
comment: Found in vertebrates, plants and Flavobacterium. Generally cytosolic, commonly activated by thiol compounds. Type example of peptidase family S9.
